## Resumen

App móvil Expo + backend Node propio. JWT-based auth. TanStack Query para data fetching.

## Capas

```
presentation/ → domain/ → data/api/ → Backend Node
```

## HTTP client (ky)

```typescript
// data/api/client.ts
import ky from "ky";
import * as SecureStore from "expo-secure-store";

export const api = ky.create({
    prefixUrl: process.env.EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL,
    hooks: {
        beforeRequest: [async (req) => {
            const token = await SecureStore.getItemAsync("token");
            if (token) req.headers.set("Authorization", `Bearer ${token}`);
        }],
        afterResponse: [/* refresh token logic */],
    },
});
```

## Auth flow

1. Login: POST `/auth/login` → recibe `{ token, refreshToken }`.
2. Tokens en `expo-secure-store`.
3. Cada request lleva `Authorization: Bearer <token>` (auto vía interceptor).
4. 401 → intenta refresh; si falla → logout.

## TanStack Query patterns

```typescript
// domain/hooks/budgets.ts
export const useBudgets = () => useQuery({
    queryKey: ["budgets"],
    queryFn: () => budgetsApi.list(),
});
```

